<br>
I relish the challenge. Sure the barbarians fear us, after all they only have a single well for their water source. The rangers of surefall hate us for diseasing their bears and wolves. <br>
<br>
The paladins of Qeynos hate us for corrupting the guards and placing Antonius Bayle in a compromising position. <br>
<br>
Verant did a good job with this diety. We should be hated and feared. Life should be hard. I would have liked to see undead being a bit more friendly towards us though. I would have liked to see more quests that were Bertox based.<br>
<br>
The Plague Lord is the one diety that even other gods fear and respect. His corrupting influence has touched the gnomes. We have played a role with the Iksar.<br>
<br>
What is the worship of Hate, Glory, Love, Justice or Fear but the worship of transitory states. Bertox is the end of everything.<br>
<br>
(Course it is hard to RP someone so different than myself over time.)<br>
