<br>
As is the case with me.  I am a devoute disciple of Lord Cazic-Thule, the Faceless.  Through me, Lord Cazic-Thule spreads Dread, Fright and Terror across Norrath.  In my studies of Fear, I have come to know a great deal about cowardice.  Fear doesn't exist without the fearless and the cowardly.  I myself fear certain... things... and I use this thrill and panic of fear to help me understand Lord Cazic-Thule and further his will.  Disease doesn't exist without a cure.  Hatred doesn't exist without tolerance.<br>
<br>
/ooc<br>
<br>
I've played everquest for a few years now and I must say that clerics are by far the most fun I've ever had.  They're not the easiest class to play, and it is hard (but not impossible) to solo.<br>
<br>
I think that in general you will see that faction is always an issue if you're an evil character.  Don't let that get you down.  View it as a challenge.  Also, don't be afraid to try some of the more rare race/diety combinations for your clerics.  There are too many High Elf, Dwarven and Dark Elven clerics out there as is.  Who knows, maybe this will all pay off with the upcoming Planes of Power expansion, when you can run up and give Bertoxxulous a kiss on His disease-ridden, pus covered lips! <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=289462"> Izzuum Rahij</a></b><br>
