When i was on Fv test, a bunch of us had planned to make a bertoxxulous guild Sadly every member left within the first two weeks, i eventually got bored and re-rolled, i played Bertoxxulous characters for a year solid and know there history well.<br>
<br>
Once you become Kos in Qeynos move to Highhold past, Highhold is mostly Corupt, so you can gain good faction fast there and get most of your spells, food, place to bind and new good hunting grounds.<br>
<br>
Being a shadowknight of Bertoxxulous is harder than being an iksar sometimes, Iksar raise in faction's faster in some places than bertoxxulous players, with my enchanter grouped with an Teir`Dal shadowknight, the shadowknight gained faction around 8x faster for erudin/paineel than the enchanter. Both would only group at same time (2nd box before it blew up heh) Being an Bloodsabre is hard....but rewarding in it's own way.<br>
<br>
May i also point out that:<br>
<br>
1.) the undead guards that are outside the shrine, before they were normall skeletons but people used to exp off them *grins*<br>
<br>
2.) the dead paladin.... the zombie in the aquaducts, he was tortured, killed and re-animated as an example for others. (good enough show for undead powers for you?)<br>
<br>
3.) I hunted Surefall glade for bear pelts + mamoth for the rage war maul quest, those bears are a great source of pelts. Yes it screws your faction but you can use the aquadcuts to skip parts of Qeynos.<br>
<br>
4.) you can use the aquaducts, enter the arena, sneek out to the bank (corrupt guards swap duty at night) and sell inside and goto the bank even if the normal guard kos you.. because they change duty....the barbarians are another matter... i just killed them though, was more fun that way.<br>
<br>
5.) Highpass ends up your new home if you become to kos, i killed the paladins for the medalion quest, and ran every Bertoxxulous quest i could find, milenia and nerrissa hah both i think died at many points.<br>
<br>
Dont worrie about faction, i worked mine until 99% of Qeynos was kos - never had to many troubles there.<br>
